WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.160
Mango transforms digital collections into guided cinematic stories.

00:05.160 --> 00:13.160
Built natively on IIIF, Mango lets you bring images, media, and interpretation together into a single, seamless viewing experience.

00:13.160 --> 00:20.920
With multilingual support for narration and annotations, stories can reach audiences in their own language.

00:20.920 --> 00:27.760
Because Mango works directly with IIIF, every level of detail is instantly available.

00:27.760 --> 00:33.720
Stories can guide viewers through collections, highlighting the details that matter most.

00:33.720 --> 00:38.800
Mango adds interpretation directly into the visual experience.

00:38.800 --> 00:46.080
Annotations appear in context, helping explain objects, people, and moments without interrupting the story.

00:46.080 --> 00:48.800
Place annotations exactly where they are needed.

00:48.800 --> 00:54.680
Mango stories aren't limited to a single collection. Combine unlimited IIIF manifests 

00:54.680 --> 00:59.200
to build richer, cross-collection narratives.

00:59.200 --> 01:06.120
Mango supports audio and video, allowing you to focus on key moments by setting start and end times within media.

01:06.120 --> 01:12.720
Use multiple audio or video clips throughout a story to guide viewers through complex narratives.

01:12.720 --> 01:16.080
Mango enables layered storytelling.

01:16.080 --> 01:25.560
Images, annotations, narration, and video can work together, helping audiences understand not just what they are seeing, but why it matters.

01:25.560 --> 01:31.720
From education to heritage to research, Mango adapts to the story you want to tell.

01:31.720 --> 01:38.280
Mango is built on open standards, powered by IIIF, and designed for long-term digital storytelling.

01:38.280 --> 01:45.360
It gives organizations a way to turn collections into experiences without locking content into proprietary systems.

01:45.360 --> 01:48.080
This is Mango.

01:48.080 --> 01:54.200
Open collections, open standards, open storytelling.